From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 02:55:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qcom: ppe: edma: alloc err_stats in setup, not
 only in debugfs

The EDMA misc IRQ handler (edma_misc_handle_irq in edma.c) does

    struct edma_err_stats *stats = this_cpu_ptr(edma_ctx->err_stats);

at its very first instruction. But `edma_err_stats_alloc()` is only
called from `edma_debugfs_setup()` (drivers/.../edma_debugfs.c:352).
On IPQ5332 the first misc IRQ fires shortly after link-up, before
debugfs registration has run — `edma_ctx->err_stats` is still NULL,
and `this_cpu_ptr(NULL)` is a small per-CPU offset which then dies
in the handler with a paging fault at `edma_misc_handle_irq+0x1a8`.

Move the alloc into `edma_setup()` so it always runs at probe.
Remove the duplicate alloc from debugfs setup (keep the file
exposure only).

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c
@@ -918,6 +918,17 @@ int edma_setup(struct ppe_device *ppe_dev)
 		return ret;
 	}

+	/* Allocate err_stats here (not only from debugfs setup) so the
+	 * misc IRQ handler's `this_cpu_ptr(edma_ctx->err_stats)` always
+	 * resolves to a valid percpu allocation. Without this, the first
+	 * misc IRQ after link-up crashes in edma_misc_handle_irq+0x1a8.
+	 */
+	ret = edma_err_stats_alloc();
+	if (ret) {
+		dev_err(dev, "Failed to alloc edma err_stats: %d\n", ret);
+		return ret;
+	}
+
 	ret = edma_irq_init();
 	if (ret) {
 		dev_err(dev, "Error in irq initialization\n");
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_debugfs.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_debugfs.c
@@ -348,11 +348,10 @@ int edma_debugfs_setup(void)
 		goto debugfs_dir_failed;
 	}

-	/* Allocate memory for EDMA miscellaneous stats */
-	if (edma_err_stats_alloc() < 0) {
-		pr_err("Unable to allocate miscellaneous percpu stats\n");
-		goto debugfs_dir_failed;
-	}
+	/* err_stats is now allocated in edma_setup (in edma.c) so the
+	 * misc IRQ handler can rely on it before debugfs is up. Just
+	 * expose the file here.
+	 */

 	if (!debugfs_create_file("err_stats", 0444, stats_dentry,
 				 NULL, &edma_debugfs_misc_file_ops)) {
